                  <h4 style="margin-left: -20px"><img src="/raw_assets/images/doubleKidneyLogo.png"></i>The significance of the <strong>Kidney</strong></h4>
                  <p class="lead">Your kidney filters wastes and excess fluids from your blood, which are then excreted in your urine. This helps regulate the level of important minerals, such as sodium and potassium, in your body. The kidney also produces erythropoietin, which is a hormone that stimulates red blood cell production in response to falling oxygen levels.</p>
