            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                  <h4><i class="fa fa-medkit"></i>What is <strong>Kidney Failure</strong>?</h4>
                  <p class="lead">There are two types of kidney failure. Chronic kidney failure is the gradual loss of kidney function, usually occurring over months to years. Because your kidneys are highly adaptable and able to compensate for lost function, signs and symptoms may not appear until irreversible damage has occurred. Acute kidney failure develops rapidly over a few hours or a few days, most commonly in critically ill people who are already hospitalized. Although acute kidney failure requires intensive treatment, the damage may be reversible with proper treatment. Both chronic and acute kidney failure can result in end-stage renal disease (ESRD). End-stage kidney failure is fatal without dialysis or kidney transplant.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
          </div>
      </section>

